Following the revelation of his involvement with a US-based lady identified as African Doll, Gospel singer Sammie Okposo said he has made peace with God hence no man can condemn him. Recall that Sammie Okposo’s infidelity came to light after he publicly apologized to his wife and family for having an affair with another woman who claimed she was pregnant for him. However, in a new Instagram post on Wednesday, the 50-year-old singer wrote: “There is no condemnation for me I am in Christ Jesus. I am controlled not by the flesh but by the spirit of God that lives in me. Euro Surges As Record Inflation Adds Pressure On ECB Casualties confirmed As Turkey Targets PKK In Iraq, Syria “The spirit of him who raised Jesus from the dead lives in me no one can condemn me because Christ who died and was raised to life is at the right hand of God interceding for me. Nothing and no one can separate me from the love of God that is in Christ. I am justified by faith. I have peace with God through Jesus Christ. “I, therefore, walk in the spirit and I will not fulfill the lust of the flesh the grace of God that brings salvation is available, sufficient, and working for me.”